arinc 628-5

connectors
- connectors should be polarized/keyed to prevent mismates
- connectors should provide strain relief
- connectors should be environmentally sealed in areas where spills might occur
- connectors should be positive latching (prefer quick release)

cables
- en3475-401 test standard requirements
- FA 25 flam requirements

wires
- min wire gauge
- equipment/wire designators
- minimum bend radii
- hidden from passenger view
- no spare wires
- splicing guidelines (refer to AS50881)
- bundling
- bundle separation
- bundling to seat beams
